The paper deals with symmetry in combinatorial problems, which is a topic that is relevant to several subfields of computer science. However, the focus on model expansion problems and the use of first-order logic suggest that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves mathematical reasoning and the study of algorithms, which are relevant to cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of IDP, a model expansion system, suggests that cs.PL (Programming Languages) may also be relevant. Finally, the study of combinatorial problems and symmetry suggests that cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) may be a relevant sub-category as well.
